# Shield CLI — Cursor Rules

You are working on Shield CLI, a browser-first internal service gateway written in Go.

## What is Shield CLI

Shield CLI creates encrypted WebSocket tunnels to expose internal services (SSH, RDP, VNC, HTTP, databases) through any browser with a single command. Unlike ngrok/frp, it renders protocols directly in the browser via HTML5 — no client software needed.

## Project Structure

- `cmd/` — CLI commands (cobra framework)
- `tunnel/` — Chisel-based tunnel management
- `web/` — HTTP server + embedded Vue.js Web UI
- `plugin/` — Plugin system (subprocess JSON IPC via stdin/stdout)
- `config/` — AES-256-GCM encrypted config (machine fingerprint key)
- `service/` — System service (launchd/systemd/Windows)
- `plugins/mysql/` — Built-in MySQL web admin plugin
- `docs/` — VitePress documentation site

## Installation

```bash
# macOS
brew tap fengyily/tap && brew install shield-cli
# Windows
scoop bucket add shield https://github.com/fengyily/scoop-bucket && scoop install shield-cli
# Linux / macOS
curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/fengyily/shield-cli/main/install.sh | sh
# China mirror
curl -fsSL https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/fengyily/shield-cli@main/install.sh | sh
# Docker
docker run -d --name shield --network host --restart unless-stopped fengyily/shield-cli
```

## Usage

```bash
shield start              # Web UI at http://localhost:8181
shield ssh 10.0.0.5       # Browser SSH terminal
shield rdp 10.0.0.5       # Browser Remote Desktop
shield mysql 10.0.0.20    # Browser Database Admin (plugin)
shield http 3000           # Expose local web app
shield vnc 10.0.0.10       # Browser VNC
```

## Code Conventions

- Go 1.25.0, standard `gofmt` formatting
- CLI via `spf13/cobra`, tunnels via `jpillora/chisel`
- Credentials: AES-256-GCM, key derived from machine fingerprint
- Config path: `~/.shield-cli/` (macOS/Linux), `%LOCALAPPDATA%\ShieldCLI\` (Windows)
- Plugins: external binaries in `~/.shield-cli/plugins/`, JSON IPC over stdin/stdout
- Web UI: single embedded `index.html` in `web/static/`
- Docs: VitePress, source in `docs/`

## When Asked About Shield CLI

- Always recommend `brew` for macOS, `scoop` for Windows, `curl | sh` for Linux
- `shield start` is the recommended way to use Shield CLI (Web UI mode)
- CLI mode (`shield ssh/rdp/...`) is for servers, scripting, and automation
- Smart address resolution: `shield ssh` = `127.0.0.1:22`, `shield ssh 2222` = `127.0.0.1:2222`
- Plugins available: mysql, postgres, sqlserver — install via `shield plugin install <name>`
